ogenerated9\">[http://www.army.mod.uk/documents/general/20130703-A2020_Update.pdf Army 2020 Update, page 9]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n** [[Queen's Own Yeomanry]], in [[Newcastle upon Tyne]] with [[Land Rover Wolf#Weapons Mount Installation Kit|Land Rover RWMIK]] reconnaissance vehicles (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with Light Dragoons)<ref name=\"autogenerated9\" />\n** 2nd Battalion, [[Yorkshire Regiment|The Yorkshire Regiment (14th/15th, 19th and 33rd/76th Foot)]], in Catterick with [[Ocelot (vehicle)|Foxhound]] vehicles (rotates to [[British Forces Cyprus]] in 2020)<ref name=\"aff\" />\n** 4th Battalion, The Yorkshire Regiment (14th/15th, 19th and 33rd/76th Foot), in York (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 2nd Battalion, Yorkshire Regiment)\n** 1st Battalion, [[Duke of Lancaster's Regiment|The Duke of Lancaster's Regiment (Queen's, Lancashire and Border)]], in [[Weeton Barracks|Weeton]] (to move to [[Dale Barracks]])<ref name=\"ZacchiFOI\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.dropbox.com/s/t2dixk6lq6502ni/20190718-FOI06365_Zacchi_Response_Letter-ArmySec%20%283%29.pdf?dl=0|title=Army 2020 Refine changes since 2017|last=|first=|date=|website=Dropbox|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-10-10}}</ref>\n** 4th Battalion, The Duke of Lancaster's Regiment (Queen's, Lancashire and Border), in Preston (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, Duke of Lancaster's Regiment)\n** [[Royal Highland Fusiliers]], 2nd Battalion [[Royal Regiment of Scotland|The Royal Regiment of Scotland]], in [[Glencorse Barracks|Penicuik]]\n** [[52nd Lowland Volunteers|52nd Lowland]], 6th Battalion The Royal Regiment of Scotland, in [[Glasgow]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 2nd Battalion, Royal Regiment of Scotland)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whatdotheyknow.com/request/596571/response/1430033/attach/3/20190911%20FOI09576%20Lai%20Response%20Letter%20ArmySec.pdf?cookie_passthrough=1 |title=Field Army Restructuring Battalion movements |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=11 September 2019 |website=WhatDoTheyKnow |access-date=12 September 2019 |quote=2nd and 6th Battalions The Royal Regiment of Scotland have transferred to 4th Infantry Brigade from 51st Infantry Brigade}}</ref>\n\n==== 7th Infantry Brigade and Headquarters East ====\n* '''[[7th Infantry Brigade and Headquarters East]]''', in [[Cottesmore, Rutland|Cottesmore]]\n**[[1st Queen's Dragoon Guards]], in [[Robertson Barracks, Norfolk|Swanton Morley]] with [[Jackal (vehicle)|Jackal]] reconnaissance vehicles<ref>[https://www.gov.uk/government/news/the-welsh-cavalry-swap-scimitars-for-jungle-boots The Welsh Cavalry swap Scimitars for jungle boots (They are due to rerole to 'Light Cavalry' and move to Swanton Morley, in Norfolk as part of the Army 2020 restructuring exercise)]</ref>\n** [[Royal Yeomanry]], in [[London]] & the [[Midlands]] with [[Land Rover Wolf#Weapons Mount Installation Kit|Land Rover RWMIK]] and [[Jackal (vehicle)|Jackal]] reconnaissance vehicles (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Queen's Dragoon Guards)<ref>[https://www.army.mod.uk/who-we-are/corps-regiments-and-units/royal-armoured-corps/royal-yeomanry/ The Royal Yeomanry]</ref>\n**1st Battalion, [[Royal Anglian Regiment|The Royal Anglian Regiment]], in [[Royal Artillery Barracks, Woolwich|Woolwich Barracks]], [[Woolwich]]\n** 2nd Battalion, The Royal Anglian Regiment, in [[Kendrew Barracks]], [[Cottesmore, Rutland|Cottesmore]]\n** 3rd Battalion, The Royal Anglian Regiment, in [[Bury St Edmunds]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 2nd Battalion, Royal Anglian Regiment)\n** 4th Battalion [[Princess of Wales's Royal Regiment|The Princess of Wales\u2019s Royal Regiment (Queen's and Royal Hampshires)]], in [[Redhill, Surrey|Redhill]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, The Princess of Wales's Royal Regiment)\n** 1st Battalion, The Rifles, in [[Beachley Barracks|Chepstow]]<ref name=\"rgbw-association\" />{{dead link|date=July 2013}}\n** 6th Battalion, The Rifles, in [[Wyvern Barracks]], [[Exeter]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, The Rifles)<ref>[http://www.army.mod.uk/documents/general/20130703-SUMMARY_OF_ARMY_2020_RESERVE_STRUCTURE_AND_BASING.pdf Summary of Army 2020 Reserve Structure and Basing, page 24] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203193356/http://www.army.mod.uk/documents/general/20130703-SUMMARY_OF_ARMY_2020_RESERVE_STRUCTURE_AND_BASING.pdf |date=2013-12-03 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.army.mod.uk/documents/general/20130703-A2020_Update.pdf Army 2010 Update, page 9]{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==== 11th Infantry Brigade and Headquarters South East ====\n* '''[[11th Infantry Brigade and Headquarters South East]]''', in [[Aldershot Garrison|Aldershot]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.army.mod.uk/who-we-are/formations-divisions-brigades/1st-united-kingdom-division/11th-infantry-brigade-and-headquarters-south-east/|title=11th Infantry Brigade and HQ South East - British Army}}</ref>\n** 1st Battalion, [[Coldstream Guards]] in [[Victoria Barracks, Windsor|Victoria Barracks]], [[Windsor, Berkshire|Windsor]]\n** 1st Battalion, [[Irish Guards]] in [[Cavalry Barracks, Hounslow|Cavalry Barracks]], [[Hounslow]]\n**[[The London Regiment]] (Army Reserve - not paired with single battalion, providing support to both 1 COLD GDS and IRISH GDS)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.army.mod.uk/who-we-are/corps-regiments-and-units/infantry/london-regiment/|title=London Regiment|website=www.army.mod.uk|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n** 1st Battalion, [[Royal Irish Regiment (1992)|The Royal Irish Regiment (27th Inniskilling, 83rd, 97th and Ulster Defence Regiment)]] in [[Clive Barracks]], [[Shropshire]]\n** 2nd Battalion, The Royal Irish Regiment (27th Inniskilling, 83rd, 97th and Ulster Defence Regiment) in [[Thiepval Barracks]], [[Lisburn]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, Royal Irish Regiment)\n** 3rd Batta