_min = 53 | lat_dir = N\n    | lon_deg = 00 | lon_min = 54 | lon_dir = E\n  }}\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom\n    | label = <small>[[Bulford|'''3 (UK) Div.'''<br />12 Armoured<br />20 Armoured]]</small>\n    | position = bottom\n    | background = white\n    | mark = Green pog.svg\n    | lat_deg = 51 | lat_min = 13 | lat_dir = N\n    | lon_deg = 01 | lon_min = 46 | lon_dir = W\n  }}\n{{Location map~ | United Kingdom\n    | label = <small>[[Tidworth Camp|1 Armoured]]</small>\n    | position = top\n    | background = white\n    | mark = Green pog.svg\n    | lat_deg = 51 | lat_min = 14 | lat_dir = N\n    | lon_deg = 01 | lon_min = 40 | lon_dir = W\n  }}\n  {{Location map~ | United Kingdom\n    | label = <small>[[Aldershot Garrison|101 Logistic]]</small>\n    | position = right\n    | background = white\n    | mark = Purple pog.svg\n    | lat_deg = 51 | lat_min = 15 | lat_dir = N\n    | lon_deg = 0 | lon_min = 45 | lon_dir = W\n  }}\n}}\n\n=== 3rd (United Kingdom) Division ===\nDivision referred to as the \"Reaction Force\"\n* '''[[3rd Division (United Kingdom)|3rd (United Kingdom) Division]]''',<ref name=\"Army 2019\" /> in [[Bulford Camp|Bulford]] (Reaction Forces)\n** [[Royal Wessex Yeomanry]], in [[Bovington Camp|Bovington]] (Army Reserve \u2013 [[Challenger 2]] crew replacement for any of the tank regiments below)\n** Pre-Hospital Care Group (from [[2nd Medical Brigade (United Kingdom)|2 Medical Brigade]])<ref name=ZacchiFOI />\n\n==== 1st Armoured Infantry Brigade ====\n* ''' [[1st Armoured Infantry Brigade (United Kingdom)|1st Armoured Infantry Brigade]]''', in [[Tidworth Camp|Tidworth]] (to become 1st Strike Brigade in 2019).\n** [[Royal Tank Regiment]], in Tidworth with Challenger 2 [[main battle tanks]] (to transfer to 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)<ref name=\"RTR19\">{{cite web|url=http://www.royaltankregiment.com/Uploads/Files/en-GB/20170317-RTR%20ERE%20SPRING%2017%20UPDATE-O.PDF|title=RTR ERE SPRING 17 UPDATE|publisher=Royal Tank Regiment Association|accessdate=31 May 2017}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n** 1st Battalion, [[Mercian Regiment|The Mercian Regiment (Cheshire, Worcesters and Foresters, and Staffords)]], in Bulford with [[Warrior tracked armoured vehicle|Warrior]] tracked [[infantry fighting vehicles]] (to transfer to 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)\n** 4th Battalion, The Mercian Regiment (Cheshire, Worcesters and Foresters, and Staffords), in [[Wolverhampton]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, Mercian Regiment, to transfer to 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)\n** 1st Battalion, [[Royal Regiment of Fusiliers|The Royal Regiment of Fusiliers]], in Tidworth with Warrior tracked infantry fighting vehicles (to transfer to 20th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)<ref name=\"Fusiliers' Website\">{{cite web|url=http://thefusiliers.org/the-colonels-christmas-message-and-news-of-regimental-growth/|title=News of Regimental growth, in the Colonel's Christmas Message|work=Fusiliers' Website|accessdate=22 December 2016}}</ref>\n** 5th Battalion, The Royal Regiment of Fusiliers, in [[Newcastle upon Tyne|Newcastle]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, Royal Regiment of Fusiliers, to transfer to 20th Armoured Brigade in 2019)<ref name=\"Fusiliers' Website\" />\n\n[[File:3rd (UK) Division 2018.png|thumb|right|upright=1.5|Structure of 3rd (UK) Division under Army 2020 Refine]]\n\n==== 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade ====\n* '''[[12th Armoured Infantry Brigade (United Kingdom)|12th Armoured Infantry Brigade]]''', in [[Bulford]]\n** [[Royal Lancers|The Royal Lancers (Queen Elizabeth's Own)]], in [[Catterick Garrison|Catterick]], with [[FV107 Scimitar]] reconnaissance vehicles (to be equipped with [[Ajax (Scout SV)|Ajax]], become an armoured cavalry regiment, transfer to the Strike Experimentation Group and move to Warminster)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://delhispearman.org.uk/notice-of-regimental-amalgamation-5thjuly-2012/|archiv