esters and Foresters, and Staffords)]], in Bulford with [[Warrior tracked armoured vehicle|Warrior]] tracked [[infantry fighting vehicles]] (to transfer to 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)\n** 4th Battalion, The Mercian Regiment (Cheshire, Worcesters and Foresters, and Staffords), in [[Wolverhampton]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, Mercian Regiment, to transfer to 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)\n** 1st Battalion, [[Royal Regiment of Fusiliers|The Royal Regiment of Fusiliers]], in Tidworth with Warrior tracked infantry fighting vehicles (to transfer to 20th Armoured Infantry Brigade in 2019)<ref name=\"Fusiliers' Website\">{{cite web|url=http://thefusiliers.org/the-colonels-christmas-message-and-news-of-regimental-growth/|title=News of Regimental growth, in the Colonel's Christmas Message|work=Fusiliers' Website|accessdate=22 December 2016}}</ref>\n** 5th Battalion, The Royal Regiment of Fusiliers, in [[Newcastle upon Tyne|Newcastle]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1st Battalion, Royal Regiment of Fusiliers, to transfer to 20th Armoured Brigade in 2019)<ref name=\"Fusiliers' Website\" />\n\n[[File:3rd (UK) Division 2018.png|thumb|right|upright=1.5|Structure of 3rd (UK) Division under Army 2020 Refine]]\n\n==== 12th Armoured Infantry Brigade ====\n* '''[[12th Armoured Infantry Brigade (United Kingdom)|12th Armoured Infantry Brigade]]''', in [[Bulford]]\n** [[Royal Lancers|The Royal Lancers (Queen Elizabeth's Own)]], in [[Catterick Garrison|Catterick]], with [[FV107 Scimitar]] reconnaissance vehicles (to be equipped with [[Ajax (Scout SV)|Ajax]], become an armoured cavalry regiment, transfer to the Strike Experimentation Group and move to Warminster)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://delhispearman.org.uk/notice-of-regimental-amalgamation-5thjuly-2012/|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130505152240/http://delhispearman.org.uk/notice-of-regimental-amalgamation-5thjuly-2012/|url-status=dead|archive-date=5 May 2013|title=9th/12th Charitable Associ