ws|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/northern-ireland/regiments-to-change-bases-in-major-army-restructure-35298093.html|title=Regiments to change bases, in major Army restructure|newspaper=Belfast Telegraph|accessdate=22 December 2016}}</ref><ref name=ZacchiFOI />\n** 2nd Battalion, [[Duke of Lancaster's Regiment|The Duke of Lancaster's Regiment (Queen's, Lancashire and Border)]], in Aldershot<ref name=\"Dec162\"/><ref name=\"Belfast Telegraph\"/>\n** 4th Battalion, [[The Rifles]], in [[Aldershot Garrison|Aldershot]]<ref name=\"rgbw-association\">[http://www.rgbw-association.org.uk/newsletter2013.pdf The Rifles and The Royal Gloucestershire,Berkshire and Wiltshire Regiment Newsletter 2013]  {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130727183131/http://www.rgbw-association.org.uk/newsletter2013.pdf |date=July 27, 2013 }}</ref><ref name=\"Dec162\">{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Commons/2016-12-15/HCWS367/|title=Strategic Defence and Security Review \u2013 Army: Written statement \u2013 HCWS367|publisher=Hansard|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref>\n** 3rd Battalion, [[Royal Gurkha Rifles|The Royal Gurkha Rifles]], in Aldershot<ref>{{cite web |title=New specialist Gurkha battalion established |url=https://www.army.mod.uk/news-and-events/news/2019/03/new-specialist-gurkha-battalion-established/ |publisher=British Army |accessdate=8 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==== 1st Intelligence Surveillance and Reconnaissance Brigade ====\n* '''[[1st Intelligence Surveillance and Reconnaissance Brigade]]''', in [[RAF Upavon|Upavon]]\n** 1 Military Intelligence Battalion, in [[Catterick Garrison|Catterick]]\n** 2 Military Intelligence Battalion, in [[RAF Upavon|Upavon]]\n** ''3 Military Intelligence Battalion, in London (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1 Military Intelligence Battalion)''\n** 4 Military Intelligence Battalion, in [[Bulford Camp|Bulford]], supporting 3 (UK) Division and 16 AA Brigade<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.army.mod.uk/who-we-are/corps-regiments-and-units/intelligence-corps/4-military-intelligence/|title=4 Military Intelligence|website=www.army.mod.uk|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-11-03}}</ref>\n** ''5 Military Intelligence Battalion, in [[Edinburgh]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 1 Military Intelligence Battalion)''\n** ''6 Military Intelligence Battalion, in [[Manchester]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 2 Military Intelligence Battalion)''\n** ''7 Military Intelligence Battalion, in [[Bristol]] (Army Reserve \u2013 paired with 4 Military Intelligence Battalion)<ref name=\":2\" />''\n** [[13 Signal Regiment (United Kingdom)|13th Signal Regiment (Cyber and Electromagnetic Activity)]] - being raised<ref>{{cite web|url=https://royalsignals.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/20170921-Master-of-Signals-Presentation.pdf|title=Royal Signals: Leaders in a Digital Age|date=1 October 2018|website=royalsignals.org|publisher=Royal Signals|access-date=16 August 2019}}</ref><ref name=ZacchiFOI />\n** [[14 Signal Regiment (Electronic Warfare)|14th Signal Regiment (Electronic Warfare)]], [[Cawdor Barracks]]{{cn|date=January 2020}}\n** [[5th Regiment Royal Artillery]], in [[Larkhill]] (Surveillance and Target Acquisition Regiment)\n** [[Honourable Artillery Company]], in [[Artillery Ground|London]] (Army Reserve \u2013 reserve surveillance and target acquisition unit, paired with 5th Regiment Royal Artillery)\n** [[32 Regiment Royal Artillery|32nd Regiment Royal Artillery]], in [[Larkhill]] with [[Lockheed Martin Desert Hawk|Desert Hawk III]] [[unmanned aerial vehicles]]<ref name=\"Dec162\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/WessexGunners/posts/2410582212534317|title=32 Regiment Royal Artillery - Wessex Gunners|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2019-10-08}}</ref>\n** [[Artists Rifles|21 (Artists) Special Air Service Regiment]], in London (Army Reserve)\n** [[23 Special Air Service Regiment (Reserve)|23 Special Air Service Regiment]], in [[Birmingham]] (Army Reserve)\n** Land Intelligence Fusion Centre, [[Hermitage, Berkshire|Hermitage]]\n** Defence Cultural Specialist Unit, Hermitage\n** Weapons Material and Personnel Exploitation Capacity, Hermitage\n** Specialist Group Military Intelligence, Hermitage\n\n==== 1st (United Kingdom) Signal Brigade ====\n* '''[[1st Signal Brigade (United Kingdom)|1st (United Kingdom) Signal Brigade]]''', in [[Innsworth]]\n** 299 Signal Squadron (Special Communications), in [[Bletchley]] supports{{citation needed|date=August 2019}} the [[United Kingdom|UK]]'s [[Foreign and Commonwealth Office]]\n** 22nd Signal Regiment, in [[Stafford]] supports NATO's Allied Rapid Reaction Corps\n** 30th Signal Regiment, in Stafford supports the PJHQ's deployable Joint Force Headquarters, Very High Readiness Field Hospital, the Air Assault Task Force and Joint Helicopter Command (to move to [[Beacon Barracks]])<ref name=ZacchiFOI /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.army.mod.uk/who-we-are/formations-divisions-brigades/6th-united-kingdom-division/1st-signal-brigade/ |title=1st Signal Brigade |date=6 September 2019 |website=army.mod.uk |publisher=British Army |access-date=6 September 2019}}</ref>\n** ARRC Support Battalion, in Innsworth supports [[NATO]]'s Allied Rapid Reaction Corps\n** ''ARRC Military Police Battalion, in [[Winchester]] (Army Reserve)''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apply.army.mod.uk/what-we-offer/army-reserve-centres/south-east/winchester-worthy-down|title=Bray House - Winchester - Worthy Down - British Army Jobs|website=apply.army.mod.uk|access-date=2019-11-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/d/viewer?mid=1nM_Rgx_0WiMOspeCiA61vqxu97Y|title=Army Reserve Units|website=Google My Maps|access-date=2019-11-04}}</ref>\n\n==== 11th Signal Brigade and Headquarters West Midlands ====\n* '''[[11th Signal Brigade and Headquarters West Midlands]]''', in [[Donnington, Telford|Donnington]]\n** National Reserve Headquarters, Royal C